            <additions>
              <p/>
              <list>
                <item xml:id="addition1" n="1">
                  <label>Colophon</label>
                  <locus from="255a"/>
                  <p>The scribe <persName>Thomas</persName> mentions his name in
                                        the concluding words:</p>
                  <p>
                    <quote xml:lang="syr">ܟܠ ܕܩ̇ܪܐ ܒܟܬܒܐ ܗܢܐ ܢܨ̇ܠܐ ܥܠ ܬܐܘܡܐ ܡܚܝܠܐ ܕܟܬ̣ܒ ܐܝܟ ܚܝܠܗ. ܕܢܬܚ̣ܢܢ ܒܝܘܡ ܕܝܢ̣ܐ ܐܝܢ
                                            ܘܐܡܝܢ.</quote>
                  </p>
                  <p>Just below, apparently in
                                        the same handwriting, but in a more cursive character, is
                                        written:</p>
                  <p>
                                        <quote xml:lang="syr">ܐܢܓܢܛܝܘܣ ܠܒܝܫ ܠܐܠܗܐ. ܚܙܐ ܒܓܠܝܢܐ ܐܠܗܝܐ
                                            ܠܚܝ̈ܠܘܬܐ ܥ̈ܠܝܐ ܕܡܙܡܪ̈ܝܢ ܒܬܪ̈ܬܝܢ ܓܘ̈ܕܐ̣. ܘܗ̣ܘ ܐܫܠܡ ܠܥܕܬܐ
                                            ܩܕܝܫܬܐ ܕܐܠܗܐ ܕܗܟܢܐ ܬܙܡ̇ܪ.</quote>
                                    </p>
                </item>
                <item xml:id="addition2" n="2">
                  <locus from="255a"/>
                  <p>A note on the same page informs us that the manuscript was
                                        collated by the deacons <persName>Abraham</persName> and
                                            <persName>Joseph</persName>:</p>
                  <p>
                                        <quote xml:lang="syr">ܦܚ̇ܡܘ ܕܝܢ ܟܬܒܐ ܗܢܐ ܐܒܪܗܡ ܘܝܘܣܦ
                                            ܡܫ̈ܡܢܫܐ. ܟܠ ܕܩ̇ܪܐ ܢܨ̇ܠܐ ܥܠܝܗܘܢ̣ ܕܢܬܚ̇ܢܢܘܢ ܒܝܘܡ ܕܝܢ̣ܐ ܐܝܟ
                                            ܓܝ̇ܣܐ ܕܡܢ ܝܡܢܝܐ̣ ܐܡܝܢ.</quote>
                                    </p>
                </item>
                <item xml:id="addition3" n="3">
                  <locus from="255b"/>
                  <p>On fol. 255 b is a note stating that this was one of the
                                        volumes brought to the <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/360">convent of S. Mary
                                            Deipara</placeName> by the abbat <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/647">Moses of
                                                <placeName>Nisibis</placeName>
                    </persName>, <date datingMethod="Seleucid" when-custom="1243">A. Gr. 1243</date>, <date calendar="Gregorian" when="0932">A.D. 932</date>.</p>
                </item>
              </list>
